          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The secondary Be-11 beam was produced by fragmentation",
                "of a 65 MeV/nucleon 15N beam from the GANIL cyclotron,",
                "which bombarded a carbon target of thickness",
                " 1.03-g/cm**2 located between the two superconducting",
                "solenoids of the SISSI device. The Be-11 beam was",
                "analyzed by the alpha spectrometer, which was operated",
                "as a fragment separator and had a 215-mg/cm**2 aluminum",
                "achromatic degrader to reject unwanted ion species.",
                "For the H-1(N-15,N-14)H-2 reaction, the N-15 primary",
                "beam was degraded in energy by a 745-mg/cm**2 carbon",
                "foil in SISSI to 584 MeV"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  magnetic spectrometer (SPEG) (see Nucl.Instr.",
                "  Meth. A276 (1989) 509-520)).",
                "Unambiguous particle identification was achieved",
                "through a combination of the energy-loss signal from",
                "an ionisation chamber, the light output from a stopping",
                "plastic scintillator."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " a thick plastic scintillator."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The angles of the incident beam particles were",
                "measured event-by-event using two position sensitive",
                "drift chambers. The combined efficiency of the two",
                "chambers was approximately 88% for the Be-11 beam and",
                " 96% for the N-15 beam.",
                "A position-sensitive microchannel detector was used as",
                "a diagnostic device."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PSSCN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The recoiling deuterons were detected in an",
                "array of ten position-sensitive sheet-resistive silicon",
                "detectors(CHARISSA). Each detector was 5*5-cm**2 in",
                "area and 500-mum thick."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".Vibrational coupling model."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Data in coincidence with the CHARISSA detector were",
                "corrected for the variation of geometrical deuteron",
                "detection efficiency as a function of the heavy ion",
                "laboratory angle."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
